genresAdvancedInfo.name: musique traditionnelle comorienne
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Musique traditionnelle comorienne is a genre of music from the Comoros Islands, an archipelago off the coast of East Africa. It is heavily influenced by Arabic, African, and Indian music, and features the use of traditional instruments such as the gambusi (a type of lute) and the ndzendze (a percussion instrument). The lyrics often focus on themes of love, nature, and everyday life.
